There are currently lively discussions on the particular issue between developing countries and industrialized countries.
The United States has already indicated that it does not want to negotiate on precise figures for the time being, although it tends to agree that, compared to the 1990 situation, by 2020 the emissions of greenhouse gases will decrease by 25 to 40 percent.
