The Six Percent of Hungary
On behalf of Hungary, Minister of Environment and Hydrology G<0xC3><0xA1>bor Fodor supports the EU’s efforts to maintain its leading role in global climate protection and to promote the signing of the new international agreement until 2009.
The minister stated that the EU is committed to reducing its gas emissions by 20 percent from the 1990 level, responsible for the greenhouse effect, regardless of whether or not the "post-2012 agreement" will be signed, and is willing to commit to its capacity to decrease its development by as much as 30 percent, and is also willing to commit to its capacity to reduce its capacity to even 30 percent if the other large developed regions see disparities in the world and countries.
