What insurance is right for me?
Car insurance, which covers the driver in the event of possible injuries, is an important expense that will depend on various factors, such as age, sex, age of the carnival, the civil status, the type of vehicle to be insured or the use of the carnival, among others.
Having a car is just the beginning.
Choosing the right car insurance is even more difficult than choosing the vehicle model.
First of all, we need to be clear about what we are talking about.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and the insured.
This commitment is materialized in an insurance contract, which states that the company receives the value of the agreed premium in exchange for being liable for the obligation to pay compensation in the event of failure.
The premium is the price of the insurance, which is established taking into account various factors, such as age, sex, age of the carnival, civil status, the type of vehicle to be insured or the use of it, among others.
Insurance companies set their prices based on the statistics, so that the more likely you are to suffer an accident, the higher the fee to pay.
That is why both women and women over the age of 25 have to pay lower premiums, as the statistics reflect that they have a lower rate of accidents due to their prudence.
Also, by using the counts, companies have come to the conclusion that married people tend to have fewer accidents than single drivers.
The use given to the vehicle will affect the frequency, and thus the probability of having some kind of parcel.
As the frequency increases, the odds increase.
There are many variables that insurers take into account when setting the premium price.
It is for this reason that the driver must study the situation well in order to choose the car insurance that best fits his profile.
Here we will expose the most significant variables when choosing one type of insurance, so that it, in addition to adapting to the characteristics of the insured, offers you a reasonable price.
Young people under the age of 25 are faced with various drawbacks when it comes to hiring affordable insurance, such as reduced driving experience and the age of the carnival.
Although the ideal to be well insured is full risk insurance, there are other more economical options.
The most cautious drivers can opt for an all-risk franchise, so they get insurance coverage at all-risk but at a more feasible price.
This kind of agreement would imply that the customer pays a portion of the amount of the sinister.
“The part of the amount of the sinister that the customer contributes will be preset based on the value of the premium, which will be higher the lower the amount,” explains Luis Noguera, Spain’s top manager of First Europa, an online insurance broker.
Another option is an extended third-party insurance, so that the customer ensures protection against damage caused to third parties, although not against those caused in his own car.
In addition, it would be covered by theft, fire and loss of the vehicle.
A piece of advice.
If you are under 25 try to be careful and avoid injuries as much as possible, as this will affect the bonus, potentially reducing the cost of insurance in the future.
A bonus is a reduction on the base rate that the company owns.
On the contrary, a penalty is a surcharge on that base fee.
The bonuses and penalties will depend on the company and its profit.
If the company has had a good year, it can afford to increase the bonuses," explains Noguera.
After 25 years, it is easier for drivers to hire insurance, since the accident rate is reduced thanks to the accumulated experience.
For this reason, it is most advisable to hire a full risk with franchise.
“Usually, young people cannot make use of the experience previously acquired at the time of being involved in an accident, and even at the time of driving,” says the director of the European company in Spain, adding that most accidents occur in the second year of driving, once the ‘novice fear’ has passed.
However, if the client is married but does not yet have children, it is preferable to negotiate insurance at all risk, as long as your financial situation allows it, of course.
Marriages with children, on the other hand, are considered by insurers as the public with the lowest rate of insolvency, so the surcharges will be lower.
In this case, the best insurance would be one at all risk with a deductible (may be 300 euros), or, when a high level of bonus is available, one to third parties extended from the third year of life of the vehicle.
“They carry on a more relaxed drive and have a greater purchasing power to afford the luxury of assuming a greater amount of franchise,” said Luis Noguera.
For pensioners it is advisable to have a full-risk insurance with a deductible (this being 150 euros), or one to third parties extended when you have a high level of bonus.
It must be said that car insurance is something important, not only because it covers the driver in the event of possible damage, but also because it represents an important expense, which is why it is essential to properly study the insurance that suits us most according to our personal situation.
